			<link>http://www.scienzaludica.it/index.php?mact=News,cntnt01,detail,0&amp;cntnt01articleid=3&amp;cntnt01returnid=102</link>
			<guid>http://www.scienzaludica.it/index.php?mact=News,cntnt01,detail,0&amp;cntnt01articleid=3&amp;cntnt01returnid=102</guid>
			<pubDate>Thu, 18 Dec 2008 15:26:25 +0000</pubDate>
			<category><![CDATA[Eventi]]></category>
			<description><![CDATA[RoboLego projectWe are writing to offer you the possibility of participating in a free European refresher course aimed at all teachers who wish to learn a new...
			We are writing to offer you the possibility of participating in a free European refresher course aimed at all teachers who wish to learn a new didactic methodology using play as a way of learning. Attached herewith, you will find a complete description of the course. It will be held in Italy, in Pistoia (a Tuscan city close to Florence) from 03/04/2009 to 10/04/2009. The course is financed by the European Union, as it is a Comenius/Grundtvig In-Service Training for teachers. The deadline for application is January 2009; it should be filled in adhering to the regulations set by your National Agency and should be signed by the Headmaster of your school. This course seeks to develop understanding of and between various European cultures through exchanges and co-operation between schools in different countries. We believe that this could be an important way for teachers from the EU to exchange experience. [more] ]]></description>
		</item>
